CGATT.description: Register (attach) the MT to, or deregister (detach) the MT from the GPRS service.

CGMR.description: Return the firmware version of the module

CGREG?.description: Read the GPRS network registration information.

CGREG.description: Configure the GPRS network registration information.

CIMI.description: Request the IMSI (International Mobile Subscriber Identity).

COPS.description: Force and attempt to use a particular carrier

CMEE.description: Configure the formatting of the result code +CME ERROR: <err> as an indication of an error relating to the functionality of the MT.

CMER.description: Configures sending of URCs from MT to DTE for indications.

CMGF.description: Indicates to the MT which input and output format of messages shall be used.

CNUM.description: Return the MSISDNs related to this subscriber.

CNMI.description: Select the procedure to indicate the reception of a new SMS in case of the MT is active

CSQ.description: Returns the radio signal strength <signal_power> and <qual> from the MT.

IPR.description: Specify the data rate the DCE accepts commands on the UART interface.

UPSD.description: Set or read all the parameters in a specific packet switched data (PSD) profile

UPSDA.description: Performs the requested action for the specified PSD profile.

UPSND.description: Return the current (dynamic) network-assigned or network-negotiated value of the specified parameter forthe active PDP context associated with the specified PSD profile.

UPSV.description: Set the UART power saving configuration

USOCO.description: Establish a peer-to-peer connection of the socket to the specified remote host on the given remote port

USOCL.description: Closes the specified socket, like the BSD close routine.

USOCR.description: Creates a socket and associates it with the specified protocol (TCP or UDP), returns a number identifying thesocket.
